Description
-----------
HeartBeat Logger is a logging and health-monitoring service for systemd-managed
services on a Raspberry Pi. It captures logs, detects crashes, failures, restart
loops, and out-of-memory events, groups repeated problems into incidents, and
stores everything in a compact local SQLite database with built-in retention. A
command-line interface is provided to inspect service health, crashes, and logs.

